text: hi guys it's angel today I'm super
excited because I'm partnering color to
make one of my favorite breakfast bowl
recipes so I'm going to be using one of
my go-to drink ingredients matcha of
course and combining it with Kellogg's
Frosted mini wheats to make a matcha
morning cereal bowl complete with matcha
with milk now I love matcha latte so
this is just another fun and delicious
way that I can get my morning pick-me-up
and breakfast when there's just no time
for coffee or tea so if you guys are
interested keep watching first let's
start with the ingredients we'll need
half a teaspoon of matcha powder and if
you're not familiar with matcha it's
just green tea leaves that have been
finely milled into a powdered form now I
always like to add a little fruit to my
cereal so I'm going to slice and prepare
half a ripe banana
next let's make the matcha infused milk
add your matcha powder to a mixing bowl
along with half a cup of cold skim milk
then with the matcha whisk or a regular
whisk mix the milk and watch it together
until well blended funny thing is I find
this part to be really fun and
therapeutic next let's combine the
ingredients into our cereal bowl I'm
using one serving of frosted mini-wheats
which is about one cup then pour in our
matcha infused milk add to the side our
sliced bananas and finally top it off
with half a teaspoon of flax seed
so this is how you can change that
breakfast with a matcha morning cereal

matcha pairs really well with the
